                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2266: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="15" xml:id="d390fn15">The same, June 17, to the Ambassador
                        in Great Britain, No. 5519.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-17T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8616. The following just received from Tokio <hi rend="italic">re</hi>
                    consortium: [Here follows text of telegram of June It) from the Ambassador in
                    Japan, printed <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>]</p>
                <p>You will please do all you can to have the group representing the interest of the
                    Government to which you are accredited authorized to complete the new Consortium
                    tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
